         <abstract>
            <p>Let v&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; = v&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;i-1&lt;/sub&gt; - 2 with v&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt; given. If &lt;tex-math&gt;$v_{n - 2} \equiv 0 (\operatorname{mod} N)$&lt;/tex-math&gt; is a necessary and sufficient criterion that N = h · 2&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt; - 1 be prime, this is called a Lucasian criterion for the primality of N. Many such criteria are known, but the case h = 3A has not been treated in full generality earlier. A theorem is proved that (by aid of computer) enables the effective determination of suitable numbers v&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt; for any given N, if &lt;tex-math&gt;$h &lt; 2^n$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. The method is used on all N in the domain h = 3(6)105, n ≤ 1000. The Lucasian criteria thus constructed are applied, and all primes N = h · 2&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt; - 1 in the domain are tabulated.</p>
         </abstract>
